Steem, the STE emulating engine, written by Anthony and Russell Hayward
SSE stands for Steven Seagal Edition, Steem SSE is just an improvement on Steem
Steem is the best so why bother with the rest?
Right-click on the fast forward button to use the flashlight - see if there is really something there on a black screen
steem was created using Borland's Free C++ compiler, it is maintained with Visual C++ too
Thanks to all the people who have helped, knowingly or not, make Steem better
If a program won't run from hard drives, copy it to a disk image using the ST desktop, and it might work better
Some programs won't work if their disk is read only, always try making it read-write (or extracting the disk if it is in an archive) if you have problems
Some programs won't work with memory size set to 4Mb or 512Kb
fast forward is very useful, map it to a key using shortcuts to get the full effect
Check the new options in this SSE build: ST model, wake-up state, C1, C2, Hacks...
More programs than you think require Accurate Disk Access Times (slow) option in the Disk manager, check Hints
Steem SSE site is now http://ataristeven.exxoshost.co.uk
The source of Steem SSE is at http://sourceforge.net/projects/steemsse

[WINSCROLLERS]
maximize the window to go to fullscreen mode (directx required)
Check which fullscreen option works for you: directdraw, direct3d
Know your mc68k from your mk68901?  Download the debug build of steem and help us get those bad games working
drag a file to the Home button with right mouse button - easy shortcuts to your disks
If you are using fullscreen monochrome, turn on Options - Fullscreen Mode - Use 256 Colour mode for extra speed
Steem Boiler: Power without the price!
ST, MSA, DIM, STT, STX, IPF, CTR, SCP, PRG, TOS: Steem runs everything!
You need pasti.dll for STX images, capslib.dll for IPF and CTR images
With unrar.dll, you can use the rar format
With archiveaccess.dll, you can use the 7z format and many more
Make sure to use the latest version of Freeimage.dll or you could get upside-down pictures!

